From f6abd9e0ec067cf8a35baf4a33d5bdb74ef70644 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Md Arif <111168803+sabamdarif@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 21:27:43 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] fix UNO bridge RTTI lookup scope on Bionic (aarch64)

The aarch64 UNO C++ bridge resolves exception type_info via a handle
from dlopen(nullptr). On glibc that handle's dlsym searches the global
scope and finds the weak _ZTIN3com3sun4star... exception type_info
symbols exported by dynamically-loaded UNO component libraries. On
Bionic that handle only searches the main executable's local group, so
the lookup fails and getRtti() fabricates a fresh type_info at a new
address.

Because libc++abi matches catch clauses by type_info pointer identity,
a fabricated type_info matches neither the typed catch (e.g.
io::IOException) nor its base uno::Exception: this patch uses
RTLD_DEFAULT (global-scope search) on Android for the lookup, otherwise
UNO exceptions raised through the bridge escape every typed handler and
reach std::terminate -> abort.

Still required with the package-wide -Wl,-z,global linking: DF_1_GLOBAL
puts each library in the global group, which RTLD_DEFAULT searches, but
the dlopen(nullptr) handle's search set on Bionic never includes
libraries dlopen'd after startup.

The x86_64 and arm bridges already use RTLD_DEFAULT in their Android
branches (activated by the __ANDROID__ fixes in 0004); this brings
aarch64 in line. (Former patch 0040, minus the fabrication-path
diagnostic fprintf.)

---
 .../source/cpp_uno/gcc3_linux_aarch64/abi.cxx | 19 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+)

diff --git a/bridges/source/cpp_uno/gcc3_linux_aarch64/abi.cxx b/bridges/source/cpp_uno/gcc3_linux_aarch64/abi.cxx
index dcd27e95a..d3c7d3783 100644
--- a/bridges/source/cpp_uno/gcc3_linux_aarch64/abi.cxx
+++ b/bridges/source/cpp_uno/gcc3_linux_aarch64/abi.cxx
@@ -75,9 +75,28 @@ OUString toUnoName(char const * name) {
 
 class Rtti {
 public:
+#if defined(__ANDROID__)
+    // On Bionic, the handle returned by dlopen(nullptr) has a dlsym search
+    // scope limited to the main executable's local group (soffice.bin plus its
+    // DT_NEEDED). It does NOT see the weak _ZTIN3com3sun4star... exception
+    // type_info symbols exported by the dynamically-loaded UNO component
+    // libraries, so getRtti() below would fail its dlsym and fabricate a fresh
+    // type_info at a new address. Because libc++abi matches catch clauses by
+    // type_info pointer identity, a fabricated type_info matches neither the
+    // typed catch (e.g. css::io::IOException) nor its base css::uno::Exception,
+    // so UNO exceptions escape every typed handler and reach std::terminate.
+    //
+    // RTLD_DEFAULT performs a global-scope search (main exe + all RTLD_GLOBAL
+    // objects); combined with forcing RTLD_GLOBAL on component loads, this
+    // resolves the *real* type_info and restores correct catch matching.
+    Rtti(): app_(RTLD_DEFAULT) {}
+
+    ~Rtti() {}
+#else
     Rtti(): app_(dlopen(nullptr, RTLD_LAZY)) {}
 
     ~Rtti() { dlclose(app_); }
+#endif
 
     std::type_info * getRtti(typelib_TypeDescription const & type);
 
